page.title: 12PETS
page.content: In this agricultural community dogs abound.In a school survey there were 48 collies,mostly working farm dogs. With plenty of open country large dogs are popular -Alsatians,several Dobermann pinschers,labradors(honey and black),a Norwegian elkhound,a Pyrenean mountain dog and a large cuddlesome St. Bernard. Smaller dogs kept or bred in the area are spaniels (cocker and King Charles),dachshunds,a bearded collie,a Jack Russell,poodles and terriers (Scottish and West Highland).Mongrels too have a place in the heart of the villagers. Cats,mice,hamsters,guineapigs,rabbits gerbils,goldfish and tropical fish are kept.Show-winning budgies are bred. Horses,for pleasure and farm work, can be seen.
